<headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 27 at 3:51PM EDT  by NWS Blacksburg</headline>
<description>...A thunderstorm will impact portions of southeastern Appomattox
and southern Buckingham Counties through 415 PM EDT...
At 350 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a thunderstorm over
Evergreen, or near Appomattox, moving northeast at 35 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Buckingham...
Appomattox...
Dillwyn...
Pamplin City...
Toga...
Appomattox National Historic Park...
and Sheppards.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
